The paper deals with complexity and approximation algorithms for graph problems, which suggests categories such as cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The specific problems studied, such as Clique and Dominating Set, are classic problems in graph theory, which could also place the paper in categories such as cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry). Finally, the paper also discusses the Gap Exponential Time Hypothesis, which is a topic in computational complexity and could place the paper in cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
